data_findings.finding: Top kernel (0.69 R²) uses ensemble of 3 models: 1) SigLIP embeddings + gradient boosting ensemble (GradientBoosting, HistGradientBoosting, CatBoost, LightGBM), 2) DINOv2/v3 backbone with FiLM conditioning, 3) MVP model with TTA. Final weights: 0.45, 0.35, 0.2. Uses patch-based image processing (520px patches), PCA/PLS feature engineering, semantic text features from concept prompts, and post-processing to enforce biomass constraints.

DINOv2 dense features approach (LB 0.66): Uses DINOv2 giant model to extract patch-based features (last_hidden_state[:,1:,:]), then applies shared MLP per patch and averages predictions. Uses TTA with horizontal/vertical flips, rotations, and Gaussian blur. Trains with sharpness-aware minimization (SAM). 5-fold cross-validation with separate models per target.
